Job Details
Training managers work to ensure employees are equipped with the requisite knowledge and skills to complete their tasks successfully. They devise strategies and methods to train staff members or provide programs on job functions, the working environment, or coping skills. Training managers sometimes delegate the handling of instruction to training officers and review the quality and efficiency of their work.  These instructors may use various equipment or technologies to get the information out to employees.
Requirements
Being an excellent trainer and leaderBeing able to inspire and motivateHave good planning, presentation, time and project management skillsBeing professional, ethical and persuasiveBeing strategic, analytical, critical and creativeKnowledge and expertise in training and instructional methodBeing able to utilize presentation, computer and software applications or equipmentBeing innovative and a visionaryBeing able to develop training curriculum, documentation or manualsBeing resourceful
